data.name: Power Of Love by Huey Lewis
data.description: Get the story behind the number one smash from the 1985 blockbuster “Back to the Future."  Discussed in detail with Huey, he elaborates on his role in the film and how the song gave the band their first No.1 hit on the US Billboard Hot 100.

data.name: If You Leave by OMD
data.description: England’s energetic synth pop duo Orchestral Maneuvers in the Dark (still the greatest name for a band ever) share the laborious process of writing the classic 1986 love song "If You Leave" for John Hughes film “Pretty in Pink” and the rush against time to deliver the song before the film was locked.  With an appearance by Matty Healy of the 1975.

data.name: Take My Breath Away by Berlin
data.description: Terri Nunn, the first princess of New Wave, outlines the heart wrenching hopeless romanticism behind Berlin's number one 1986 hit “Take My Breath Away.” Not only was it a chart-topper, but it also won the Academy Award for Best Original Song as well as the Golden Globe for Best Original Song. Learn the story of this incredible track, with a cameo on “Danger Zone” by Kenny Loggins.

data.name: Footloose by Kenny Loggins
data.description: Kenny Loggins and Kevin Bacon share the story behind the iconic movie soundtrack song Footloose. Released in 1984, Footloose spent three consecutive weeks at No. 1 on the US Billboard Hot 100 and is one of the most recognizable songs recorded by Loggins. Kick off the Sunday shoes and watch the story of this 80's classic unfold.

data.name: Iris by The Goo Goo Dolls
data.description: Released in 1998, "Iris" by The Goo Goo Dolls became of of the biggest alternative rock staples of the 90s, as well as one of the biggest genre crossover hits in the history of popular music, Learn the beautiful story of John Rzeznik’s inspired composition and how it has remained in the collective psyche through its use in the film “City of Angels” to being covered by Taylor Swift.
